<body>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 2, 2026</p>

  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>Welcome to Wonder Kid. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our platform.</p>

  <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We may collect the following information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account information:</strong> name, email address, phone number when you register.</li>
    <li><strong>Facebook profile data:</strong> if you log in with Facebook, we receive your public profile name, email address, and profile picture.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, features used, and session information.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To create and manage your account.</li>
    <li>To provide educational services and track progress.</li>
    <li>To communicate with you about your account or our services.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share data only with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Service providers who help us operate our platform (e.g., hosting).</li>
    <li>Law enforcement if required by law.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Facebook Data</h2>
  <p>When you use Facebook Login, we access only the data you authorize (name, email, profile picture). We do not post on your behalf or access your friends list.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We use industry-standard security measures including HTTPS encryption and secure cookie storage to protect your data.</p>

  <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You may request to view, update, or delete your personal data by contacting us.</p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us through our platform.</p>

  <p><a href="/">Back to Home</a></p>
</body>
